Standard leave-one-out method for critiquing (in the "incremental critiquing" paper:
In each iteration, Choose the critique that is compatible with the target product
Repeat the experiment by selecting each product as the query for 10 times...


Modified version of the leave-one-out method used in "MAUT Based Critiquing":
1. Don't "leave" any case
2. Give random preferences from the user's side and one product that is compatible with the initial user
preferences as the target product. 
3. At each iteration, choose the critique that is compatible with the target product.

